\nthe enrichment pattern of the field star population. The low [alpha/Fe] ratios\nof H4 and similar metallicity field stars in Fornax give evidence that slow\nchemical enrichment environments, such as dwarf galaxies, may be the original\nhosts of alpha-depleted clusters in the halos of the Milky Way and M31.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Oct 2015 20:22:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-23"}
